    You get two positive integers n and m, and your task is to calculate the average of integers from n to m (including n and m). Round up the answer to the next integer and convert it to binaries. If n is greater than m, return -1.
    Example:
    roundedAvg(1, 5) => "11"
    roundedAvg(7, 5) => -1
    roundedAvg(10, 20) => "1111"
