class Solution {
    /**
    Everyone knows the Fibonacci sequence, it has been thoroughly studied by mathematicians in recent centuries, but what people do not know is the Tribonacci sequence. Tribonacci sequence is defined by repetition: tri (1) = 3 tri (n) = 1 + n / 2 if n is eve. tri (n) = tri (n - 1) + tri (n - 2) + tri (n + 1) if n is odd.
    For example:
    tri(2) = 1 + (2 / 2) = 2
    tri(4) = 3
    tri(3) = tri(2) + tri(1) + tri(4)
           = 2 + 3 + 3 = 8
    You are given a non-negative integer number n, you have to a return a list of the
    first n + 1 numbers of the Tribonacci sequence.
    Examples:
    tri(3) = [1, 3, 2, 8]
     */
    public List<Integer> tri(int n) {

canonical_solution:
        if (n == 0) {
            return List.of(1);
        }
        List<Integer> my_tri = new ArrayList<>(Arrays.asList(1, 3));
        for (int i = 2; i <= n; i++) {
            if (i % 2 == 0) {
                my_tri.add(i / 2 + 1);
            } else {
                my_tri.add(my_tri.get(my_tri.size() - 1) + my_tri.get(my_tri.size() - 2) + (i + 3) / 2);
            }
        }
        return my_tri;
    }
}

